    "what_description": "Centella asiatica is a perennial plant that belongs to the family Hydrocharitaceae. It is native to tropical and subtropical regions of Asia and Australia. The plant grows up to 15-30 cm in height, with oval-shaped leaves that are 2-7 cm long and have entire margins. The leaves are opposite, petiolate, and glabrous, with a distinctive hairless and waxy texture. The plant produces small, white or pale yellow flowers in summer, which are arranged in axillary spikes.",
